===========================================JSP================================24/02=============

JSP :-
--> JSP is java server page, it is used to create dynamic web pages,
it runs inside a servlet container like apache and tomcat.

JSP lifecycle:-
==> Translation Phase:-
--> JSP file is converted into servlet java file, the servlet container translates JSP into
servlet source code.

==> Compilation Phase:-
--> Generated. java file is compile to .class file.

==> Class Loading:-
--> compiled servlet class is loaded into JVM.

==> Instantization:-
--> Object of servlet class is created.

==> Initialization:-
--> The servlet containers calls INIT() in servlet.

==> Request Processing:-
--> for every request service method is called, it is called multiple times based on the no of request.

==> Destruction:-
--> when server shut down destroyed method is called once, that is used to release the resources.

Advantages of JSP:-
--> easy to create dynamic web pages.
--> Its provides built-in implicit Objects.
--> It is automatic servlet conversion.
--> It works well with servlet containers.


Drawbacks of JSP:-
--> Mixing business logic with presentation layer.
--> we can write java code inside JSP.
--> It is not good for large scale application, bcz it is difficult to manage the complex logic & it violets
separation of concern.
--> Debugging is hard:- JPS converts to servlet internally hence error some time confusing.
--> Performance delay bcz first tym JSP is accessed , translation, compilation, hence slightly delay occurs.
--> It is not modern approach,  Bcz today we use TimeLift, RestAPI, & frontend framework like react and angular.

==> Declaration tag:-
--> <%! int a = 10; %>
-->	<%! public string demo()
    {
    return "hii";
	} %>

==> Expression tag:-

--> <% = a %>
--> <% = demo() %>
==> Scriptlet tag:-
--> <% String user = request.getParameter("user"); %>
--> <% request.setAttribute("user","Gaurav"); %>
==> Directive Tag:-
--> <% @page ("page directive")
--> <% @page ("include directive")
--> <% @tag lib URL = "-----------"(library)
==> JSP Action tags
--> <JSP:format ="  ">
--> <JSP: input = "   ">
