===========================================HIBERNATE================================24/02=============

JPA:- Java Persistence API.
ORM:- Object Relational Mapping.

Advantages Of Hibernate:-
--> Reduced Boilerplate code
--> Open source
--> Mapping
--> Automatic Table creation
--> Alternative for JDBC
--> No need Exception Handling
--> Improved Performance(Cache mechanism   --first level mechanism -- second level mechanism)
--> HQL/JPQL
--> Transaction management
--> ORM tool.

==> Hibernate:-
--> Hibernate is a ORM java framework which is used to map java object to database tables.

==> Rules of Entity Class:-
--> The class should be public and non abstract.
--> All the fields should be private, hence getter and setter should be generated.
--> The class should have default constructor/zero parametrized constructor.
--> the class should implement serializable interface.
--> The class should contain one primary key.

Example 1:-
@Entity
public class School {
    @Id
    private int sid;
    private String sname;
    private rank ;

    School school = new School();
    school.setSid(123);
    school.setName(DAV);
    school.setRank(1st);


Example 2:-
@Entity
public class Library {
    @Id
    private int bookId;
    private String bookName;
    private book;


